Study found that hospitalizations from car crashes dropped 7 percent between 2003 and 20010 in the 45 states with texting bans . 
 Arizona, Texas, Montana, Missouri, and Oklahoma are the only five states in America that do not have texting at the wheel bans for all drivers . 
 The study also found that older drivers were more likely to make a texting and driving mistake than a younger driver . 
 